page.title: 01Description & Index
page.content:
An area of outstanding natural beauty, approximately 5 sq.km. of which is Chichester Harbour, running from SW to NE, with Thorney and Pilsey Islands in the NE and the land S. E. and NE being mainly farm land. East Head is a sand dune promontory in the S. and to the W. of the mainland.
The area consists of:- Chichester Harbour - Agricultural Land Itchenor Village - Houses at Rookwood, Malthouse Cottages - Redlands & Chapel Lane, W.Wittering. - Industry at Itchenor & W.Wittering - Church, Itchenor; Chapel, Wittering. Two static caravan sites in Wittering - Two clubs in Itchenor - One public house in Itchenor
